content: ReAct agent: Sam Altman is a prominent American entrepreneur, investor, and computer programmer. He co-founded Y Combinator, a startup accelerator, and served as its president from 2014 to 2019. Altman is also known for his work in artificial intelligence and has been a vocal advocate for its potential benefits and risks. He currently serves as the CEO of OpenAI, a research organization focused on developing artificial general intelligence.

ReAct agent: Paul Graham is a well-known entrepreneur, essayist, and creator of the startup incubator Y Combinator. He co-founded Y Combinator in 2005 with Jessica Livingston, and the organization has since launched over 2,000 companies. Graham's essays on entrepreneurship, startup culture, and programming have been published on his website, Paulgraham.com, since 1998. He is also an investor and advisor to various startups.
